IAST 2023 is a multi-fraternity AYUSH event, to be hosted at Nishagandhi Auditorium at Thiruvananthapuram, from 13 to 15 January 2023.

The key motive of the summit is to promote high-quality research and academic discourse on AYUSH medical systems. Conduct seminars on cost-effective AYUSH services, promotion of AYUSH systems, and strengthening of health education systems.  Quality control of Ayurveda, Siddha and Unani & Homoeopathy (ASU &H) drugs and sustainable availability of ASU & H raw materials will be addressed at the summit.

Press Network of India (PNI) a registered media society having a pan-India presence, along with Santigiri Ashram, an organization diligently promoting AYUSH across the globe and leading organisations of AYUSH practitioners like QPHA (Qualified Private Homeopath’s Association) along with likeminded organizations are organizing the summit. IMC (International Malayali Council), a prominent social and cultural organization is making every effort to make the Summit a unique success

To publicize the Summit, awareness sessions coupled with medical camps are scheduled at prominent locations: within Kerala and neighbouring states.

Medical Camps
Specialized Clinics for critical illnesses like CANCER and HEART ailments.
The Summit has over 40 specialized clinics from all departments of AYUSH- Ayurveda, Yoga and Naturopathy, Unani, Siddha and Homeopathy. The clinics are manned by specialists in critical illnesses like cancer, cardiac, kidney & liver, pulmonary and also lifestyle related. There are speciality clinics for senior citizens (geriatric ailments), women and children. There will be separate centres for traditional medicines and alternate therapy.


Highlights Of IAST 2023
3000+ Delegates and Celebrated Speakers
Over 3000 delegates from reputed health-related Institutions from India and abroad. Speakers specialized in the AYUSH system of medical science and therapy from India and abroad.

